prompt.en:
**Angajat, Programator, Manager**
Implement the class hierarchy as described in the UML diagram, so that the main() code produces the specified output.

**UML:**
Class: Angajat
Attributes:
- salariu: Integer
- nume: String
- id: Integer
Methods:
+ GetNume(): String
+ GetSalariu(): Integer
+ SetSalariu(salariu: Integer): bool
+ Lucreaza(): void
+ Angajat(nume: String, salariu: Integer, id: Integer)

Class: Programator (inherits from Angajat)
Attributes:
- cod: String
Methods:
+ Lucreaza()
+ Add(cod: String)
+ Programator(nume: String, salariu: Integer, id: Integer)
+ GetCode(): String

Class: Manager (inherits from Angajat)
Attributes:
- echipa[0..*]: Angajat
- numeEchipa: String
Methods:
+ Lucreaza()
+ Angajeaza(x: Angajat): bool
+ Concediaza(x: Angajat): bool
+ GetAngajat(id: Integer): Angajat
+ Manager(numeEchipa: String, nume: String, salariu: Integer, id: Integer)

**main():**
```cpp
int main()
{
  Programator petru("Petru", 1000, 0);
  Programator maria("Maria", 1100, 1);

  Manager mihai("C++","Mihai", 1200, 2);

  mihai.Angajeaza(&maria);
  mihai.Angajeaza(&petru);

  petru.Add("int main()\n{\n");
  maria.Add("std::cout<<\"Hello World\";\n");

  mihai.Lucreaza();

  Programator george("George", 900, 3);
  george.Add(petru.GetCode());
  george.Add(maria.GetCode());
  george.Add("\n}\n");

  mihai.Concediaza(&petru);
  mihai.Angajeaza(&george);

  mihai.Lucreaza();
}
```

**Expected output:**
```
=========
C++
=========
C++
[Maria]:
std::cout<<"Hello World";
[Petru]:
int main()
{
=========
C++
[Maria]:
std::cout<<"Hello World";
[George]:
int main()
{
std::cout<<"Hello World";
}
=========
```

